    "bio": {
      "text": "Isaiah Thomas is a fourth-year student with a dual degree in Sociology and Environment & Sustainability Studies and a minor in Studio Art at Texas Christian University. His research interests include critical theory, black studies, cultural studies, and critical geography. As an artist, Isaiah explores concepts of queer theory and visual studies primarily through photography. This summer, his work examines the relationship between urban spatial/environmental inequalities and critical theory in blackness and culture. Upon graduation, he aims to pursue a PhD in Visual and Cultural Studies.",
